# Brand and conversion doctrine

When work touches public marketing pages, landing pages, intake pages, pricing presentation, CTA wording, productized service offers, AI Lead Rescue, buyer-facing copy, or buyer-facing visual design, read and apply both the brand/conversion doctrine and the broader marketing execution standards:

- `docs/marketing/BRAND_AND_CONVERSION_DOCTRINE.md` — brand / conversion specifics (single offer rule, route after intent, AI Lead Rescue).
- `docs/marketing/00_NON_NEGOTIABLE_MARKETING_COMMUNICATION_STANDARD.md` — Hook / Proof / Depth doctrine, dual-asset pattern, aesthetic standard.
- `docs/marketing/01_AGENT_OUTPUT_CONTRACT.md` — required output header + content structure for every external-facing agent response.
- `docs/marketing/02_MULTIMODAL_CONTENT_PLAYBOOK.md` — attention / validation asset pairing, video / visual rules, proof density by funnel stage.
- `docs/marketing/03_CONTENT_ATOM_SCHEMA.md` — reusable structured marketing knowledge for AI retrieval.
- `docs/marketing/04_DELIVERY_QUALITY_GATE.md` — preflight checklist + 12/14 scoring model + handoff format.
- `docs/marketing/05_AGENT_COMPULSION_MECHANISM.md` — four-layer enforcement (source-of-truth, prompt preamble, PR checklist, automated check).

These are canonical unless a newer in-repo decision explicitly supersedes them. The brand/conversion doctrine and the execution standards are complementary, not alternatives — the brand doctrine governs the offer; the execution standards govern how the offer is communicated.

## Non-negotiable summary

- Effectiveness beats decoration.
- Clarity beats cleverness.
- Conversion beats completeness.
- The page is done only when the intended buyer understands the offer, trusts the path, and knows exactly what to do next.
- Primary CTAs must describe buyer intent, not internal process.
- Payment/routing complexity must come after buyer intent.
- For AI Lead Rescue, do not use `Choose payment path` as the primary CTA.
- Every external communication must combine attention + comprehension + proof + aesthetic discipline + a clear next action (Hook / Proof / Depth doctrine).
- Every attention asset must point to a validation asset (dual-asset pattern). Standalone hooks without a depth path are not shipped.
- No prospect-facing or client-facing work is shipped without a visible quality-gate statement (target score ≥ 12/14 per `docs/marketing/04_DELIVERY_QUALITY_GATE.md`).

## Required review before merge

Before merging buyer-facing marketing work, verify:

- One primary conversion goal is obvious.
- The offer is understandable within five seconds.
- The CTA is buyer-action-oriented.
- Payment, region, and routing complexity appears only after buyer intent.
- The page avoids unsupported revenue guarantees and exaggerated AI claims.
- The buyer knows the next step.
- The asset has Hook / Proof / Depth and a validation path (per the Agent Output Contract).
- Claims are supported or explicitly flagged as hypotheses (per the Delivery Quality Gate).
- Live production verification is recorded for customer-visible routes, following `.cursor/rules/delivery-reality.mdc`.
